snippet.textDisplay:
Ok. In this day & age of germ & virus scares -- why are you still using a wooden spoon?? Doesn't the wood hold nasties easier? Washing it tends to ruin the wood & make the spoon splinter or break. Why not use metal or silicon spoons? Longer lasting, easier to clean, & just as effective.

The recipe itself looks like a flour-free variation of the PB cookies in Joy of Cooking. Pretty much all Alton left out is the flour.

snippet.textDisplay:
The simplest cookie recipe:
1 cup peanut butter
1 cup granulated sugar
1 egg

Roughly tablespoon size balls squished with a fork on a cookie sheet

Bake at 350 for 10ish minutes.

Literally delicious I promise
